5: This appears to be our destination.
9:
Now all we have to do is hand the
chip over to the carrier, right? They
said something about him riding in
on a board...
11:
Right on time, as usual! Man, I'm
good!
14:
Hey, 'sup? You're the ones handing
off the chip, right? Where is it?
18: Thanks, man! I'll take care of the rest!
21:
Stop right there. Hand over the chip,
and nobody gets hurt!
27: Get away while you still can!
32:
Hah! Gotta say this suits me much
better than that delivery business!
39:
Phew... Thank goodness we made it
out of there in one piece.
41:
Yo, I remember you! Thanks again,
man!
44:
Ah, looks like you finished your half
of the delivery. Um... Sorry, I didn't
get your name.
48:
I'm Axem. You guys're hella strong! I
was a bit worried at first, but you
totally took care of them.
52:
Well, that thing you rode was pretty
cool too. Talk about speed! I could
hardly believe it.
57:
Wait, is this your first time seeing an
extremeboard? They're, like,
extremely popular!
60:
See? Look at this beauty! This
extremeboard here is my baby! Ain't
she the coolest thing you've ever
seen?
64:
But looks aren't all she's got! She's
equipped with DOUBLE anti-gravity
boosters and a sweet aerial
gyroscope, plus her body is made
out of special lightweight carbon!
67:
She might not be as stable or
powerful as the newest models, but
her speed and turning abilities are
second to none! My modded board
is the best in the biz!
72:
N-none of those words made any
sense to me, but am I right to
assume this board of yours is quite
impressive?
78:
You bet she is! And since I can ride
such a beast with ease, that makes
ME equally as impressive!
80:
I haven't made my debut yet, but
I've been scouted by a whole bunch
of agents, you know.
84:
So you're going to be a
professional... extremeboarder?
89:
Yup! I've already passed a hundred
thousand followers online! Pretty
sure that makes me the top
up-and-coming rookie!
94:
A hundred thousand? On Line? Is
this some new system used to
indicate power levels?
100:
You really are outta the loop, huh?
Where'd you guys come from,
anyway?
103:
Here's your order. Our brand new
SoyMate Shake.
112:
Whoa! You drank it just like that?
Aren't you gonna use an AdTaste or
something?!
116:
Hehe, wanna give it a try? You guys
really saved my skin, so it's on me!
120:
Excuse me! Can I get three more
shakes?
126:
Urk! This texture... It's like putting clay
in my mouth!
130:
Ahahaha! Pretty nasty, right? It's a
nutritious drink, but man, oh man,
does it taste like liquified exhaust
fumes!
135:
Why do you know what that tastes
like... How can you even drink this
slop anyway?
139:
Dude, AdTaste is expensive. I'd
rather spend that money on tricking
out my board.
141:
If I'm gonna go pro, I can't skimp on
the vitamins and protein. Besides, it
all goes to the same place anyway,
so I can get past the taste.
145:
W-well, I certainly admire your
dedication...
149:
But this flavor is just too terrible. I
can't allow this!
151:
Axem, have you ever signed a
non-disclosure agreement before?
158:
Whoooa! What is this? I've never
eaten something with so much
flavor before! And this is
all-natural?! I feel like a real foodie!
161:
This is probably the best meal I've
ever had! No way would I ever get
sick of this!
165:
Ah, but... I bet eating this kinda stuff
is pretty bad for you, right?
168:
Not at all. Everything here is high in
protein and low-carb!
174:
Seriously?! Aw man, you're a cooking
GOD, Alk!
178:
All I did was follow the recipes. You
know, if you lived here, you could eat
like this whenever you wanted.
183:
No kidding?! Count me in, dude!
Consider this my move-in date!
186:
Now for a quick ride around town to
celebrate!
